2.1 Library Usage
=================

The library may be used by adding `-lpihwm' when compiling on the
_Raspberry Pi_.  Programs should include `pihwm.h' and any other
hardware specific headers from the `include' directory as required.
Note that if a prefix has been specified when configuring, it may be
necessary to specify the location of the library (using the `-L' flag)
and the headers (using the `-I' flag).

For example, running on the _Raspberry Pi_:

     gcc -I/opt/pihwm/include demo.c -L/opt/pihwm/lib -l pihwm -o demo


