3.1 Setting up the  _Raspberry Pi_
==================================

For all these examples we are going to be using the _Raspberry Pi_
"headless", that is without its own keyboard, mouse and monitor. We'll
connect to it over Ethenet using the _secure shell_ (`ssh') program
from a terminal window on another computer.

All the examples will work just fine with the conventional setup with
keyboard, mouse and monitor. However you're quite likely to want to use
these circuits to control things like model cars or small robots, and
you really don't want to have to carry around anything more than a
battery.

